messages.message:
On the new validations tab for 23.45:
1. All strings should be sentence case, so like:
    a. Validation rules
    b. Apply to all
    c. Model confidence (and any other rule types we add)
2. We should consider dropping "default" from apply-to-all rules. Now that we have an apply-to-all group, calling these rules "defaults" is redundant. It's also confusing, because it's misusing the term. These apply-to-all rules might be "global" or "project-wide" but they're not "default".
